text: François Place (born 2 July 1989) is a French freestyle skier. He competed in the 2017 FIS Freestyle World Ski Championships, and in the 2018 Winter Olympics. He participated at the FIS Freestyle Ski and Snowboarding World Championships 2019, winning a medal.Ski cross results ==References== ==External links== * Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:French male freestyle skiers Category:Olympic freestyle skiers of France Category:Freestyle skiers at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:People from Albertville Category:Sportspeople from Savoie
